title: Side Chair, mid-19th century
medium: Papier-mâché, mother of pearl, caning, wood
creditline: Gift of Jennifer C. Kruger and Lucy C. Stark
description: Shaped rectangular back with an arched splat inlaid with a flower-filled basket between barley-twist turned stiles headed by finials and a serpentine caned seat, on cabriole legs with scroll feet.
